functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.

msg.content: Which planets in our solar system were discovered after 1700, and who discovered them?
Which planets in our solar system were discovered after 1700, and who discovered them?

Here are the planets discovered after 1700. Planets beyond Uranus are considered dwarf planets, and are included as well.

- Neptune (1846): John Couch Adams, Urbain Jean Joseph Le Verrier and Johann Gottfried Galle
- Pluto (1930) - Clyde William Tombaugh
- Ceres (1801) - Giuseppe Piazzi
- Pallas (1802) - Heinrich Wilhelm Olbers
- Juno (1804) - Karl Ludwig Harding
- Vesta (1807) - Heinrich Wilhelm Olbers
- Uranus (1781) - William Herschel
- Eris (2005) - Michael E. Brown, Chad Trujillo, David L. Rabinowitz
- Makemake (2005) - Michael E. Brown, Chad Trujillo, David L. Rabinowitz
- Haumea (2005) - José Luis Ortiz Moreno, Michael E. Brown, David Rabinowitz, and Chad Trujillo

Note that some planets were discovered by multiple people, this is due to the fact that the discovery process for some planets, such as Neptune, was long and collaborative.
